Personally I like to use a torrent client for downloading. I use Utorrent for all of my torrent work. It can be found directly from their site at http://www.utorrent.com/downloads

Worth mentioning, a lot of the files found in torrent downloads are compressed using WinRar. 

WinRar is a file compression utility that will unpack (extract) your new torrent download.

Also worth mentioning: Once a file is at 100% completely downloaded, it is always great to upload at least as much as you download. That practice is called sharing. You can see your share ratio in Utorrent and use that as a gauge.

Sharing (seeding) is how the peer to peer (P2P) community continues to survive.

Not sharing deems you a leech and WILL get you banned in some private torrent sites. 

Good practice...Always share :-)
